dismissalText.commentary: Mominul Haque run out (Vithanage) 60 (60b 8x4 0x6 70m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: he waits for it to turn, tucks it to deep square leg and what do we have here!! A wicket out of nowhere again. Mominul was a touch slow to turn for the second and a great throw from the deep finds him short at the non-striker's end. Direct hit it was.. Sri Lanka have a bonus wicket as Mominul was looking so good. But great work by the fielder- Vithanage - there, he went for the non-striker's end smartly..This was shaping to be such a good innings

headshotImage.caption: Ashan Priyanjan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ashan Priyanjan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain c Priyanjan b Lakmal 38 (43b 4x4 0x6 71m) SR: 88.37

dismissalComment.html: another wicket! This is the big one. Nasir Hossain hits the full toss straight to midwicket. It's all falling apart. There had been so many full tosses from Lakmal that Naeem had failed to get away. This time, Nasir shows the right intent, but doesn't manage to beat the midwicket fielder, who takes a head high catch. Some luck with those full tosses for Lakmal, but I guess, you make your own luck by bowling well. That 250-run target is distant now

and Dammika has a wicket in his first over! It's stack overflow, the blue screen of death, core dump.. as they say it! Anamul played that lovely shot earlier in the over, then started playing loose shots. This one was short of length and rising outside off, the batsman plays a nothing poke away from his body and the outside edge flies waist high to the keeper. Can't say I didn't see it coming..

headshotImage.caption: Shamsur Rahman player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shamsur Rahman  player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Dammika strikes again! It's a short ball, the first one of the day.. And it was quick too. The batsman was sucked into playing a hook shot and was no way in control of that.. A deep square leg was placed for that exact shot and it just settles into his hands.. He didn't have to move an inch.. It's good when a plan comes together..Shamsur's scratchy stay ends.

and Dammika strikes again! And now Rahim is gone! This was short and wide and asking to be hit. Rahim does that part of the job well, but he hits it straight to the man at point. Maybe he wasn't able to control that extra bounce, but unlucky that he found the fielder there. Sena does well to hold on to that as it was hit pretty hard. Another wicket from nowhere. There is an air of unpredictability about how these wickets are falling when you least expect them

headshotImage.caption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Suranga Lakmal, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalComment.html: Lakmal finally gets something in that last column of his bowling figures! The one time Mahmudullah throws his bat at the length ball, he hits it straight to long on. That pressure was building for a while and it has consumed the batsman. There is a strange uneasy buzz around the ground because the runs have been hard to come by. Mahmudullah tries to break it with one shot and perishes

dismissalText.commentary: Kusal Perera b Rubel Hossain 106 (124b 6x4 5x6 142m) SR: 85.48

dismissalComment.html: oh he runs out of luck this time! Possibly he was just tired as he throws his bat at the length ball - played completely across the line - and misses it completely. The off stump takes a beating. But what an innings this has been. He got his maiden hundred on a day his team needed extra responsibility. Well played KJP

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c Anamul Haque b Rubel Hossain 64 (70b 4x4 0x6 98m) SR: 91.42

dismissalComment.html: and Rubel gets another one! This was quick, this was pacy, this had extra zip and extra bounce. the batsman wanted to guide it to third man but is surprised by the pace on that, it takes a thick outside edge straight to the keeper. Anamul doesn't show any reaction at all first.. but I guess it was because he was confident that it was out, not the other way
a soft dismissal first ball! The crowd roars. He comes round the wicket and Thirimanne just spoons it to short cover. It possibly stopped in the pitch a bit. But a big breakthrough for Bangladesh

commentTextItems.html: and he finishes the series with style! Smashes this turning delivery over midwicket with a powerful hit to wrap the win! And the series 3-0
he appeals for lbw as Angelo offers no shot! But this is spinning down the leg side
he works this away to square leg for another easy single to bring the scores level

commentPostTextItems.html: Tharindu: "Someone said he sense a twist twice. A twist of a twist is an untwist"

commentPreTextItems.html: This has been one thorough chase by Sri Lanka, set up by Kusal Janith Perera's maiden ODI ton and a solid stand between him and Dinesh Chandimal..Bangladesh exerted some pressure in the first half of the innings with their spinners, but they didn't manage to get the wickets.. Most impressive was KJP's poise during the innings and Chandimal's skill in rotating the strike. They never really appeared hurried, helping Sri Lanka end this tour with another win. A sorry series for Bangladesh during which they failed to win a single match.. It's perfect preparation for Sri Lanka ahead of the Asia Cup, but Bangladesh will have serious concerns. We will be back next week with the Asia Cup, till then ciao ciao.
Man of the Match is Kusal Perera for his maiden century

Uwaisul Karnain: "Clinical performance by SL to wrap the series. Captain Mathews and rookie Priyanjan added the finishing touch after Kusal & Chandimal set up the run chase with a brilliant partnership."
sagar: "parera and chandimal patnership was the difference between two team. if now bd chasing this run it could be different story.... its all about planning not about experience. "

Piumal De Soysa: "Lots of things to take out of this tournament,Angelo's captaincy,Success of the middle order and the lower middle order,ground fielding and more importantly the consistency from the next tournament..Chandimal's best innings always comes in the last game of the tournament.He has loads of work to do.. Bangla need to change their approach towards the game and needs play through the small passages to gain the upperhand of the game which they have the ability but not capitalise on.."

stories.summary: The defeat to Sri Lanka in the ODI series will not make Bangladesh panic, according to their coach Shane Jurgensen, ahead of the Asia Cup and World Twenty20

recentPreviewStory.subTitle: Bangladesh v Sri Lanka, 3rd ODI, Mirpur
recentPreviewStory.seoTitle: Sri Lanka aim for sweep without Big Three
recentPreviewStory.summary: Sri Lanka have always had one of Dilshan, Sangakkara and Jayawardene in their ODI team since 1999. They will have to play the final ODI in Bangladesh without them
